pageContext.description: Cast solid. The 3 ends cast separately and welded [sic] on. The 2 ends of fork have hollow backed ends crossed by a strap. each of the 3 ends are decorated with 5 bead-like swellings and a terminal knob. The top of terminal knob of spike is neatly drilled.
pageContext.patina: Dark brown - some patches of black, metal showing through.
pageContext.associations: A find of 4 associated objects: ?yoke ornament, a bracelet, a bell and a hook with ring attached.
pageContext.collection: Museum of Archaeology and Ethnology, Cambridge,No. 248 Murray Collection
pageContext.toSearch: Boyne, Friarstown North, Fanningstown, Co. Limerick, Ireland
